name: mm
description: Performs a matrix multiplication of the matrices input and mat2.
example:
mat1 = torch.randn(2, 3)
 mat2 = torch.randn(3, 3)
torch.nn.functional.mm(mat1, mat2) 
tensor([[ 0.4851,  0.5037, -0.3633],
[-0.0760, -3.6705,  2.4784]])

inputs.name: input
inputs.description: the first tensor to be multiplied.

inputs.name: mat2
inputs.description: the second tensor to be multiplied.
